title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER 1894 DELUXE PISTOL GRIP
postcontent: From my personal collection, a desirable Winchester Model 1894 pistol grip deluxe rifle in 38-55 with 26" octagon barrel. Winchester called these "fancy sporting rifles" and this one is certainly fantastic looking in the best caliber and configuration. And it's also in the desirable early serial range for which the original factory records remain. As you can see, the metal was refinished a long time ago, so it's starting to develop a mellow aged look. The blue is about the right color and sheen, and the markings and edges remain quite sharp, slight dishing on a couple screw holes and part of the barrel address is very slightly blurred. The good news is the wood was not refinished at all, and has its original factory deluxe finish and checkering completely untouched and intact. The wood is beautiful with rich color and fantastic feather crotch figure. These original fancy H-checked stocks alone are very valuable. Because the metal finish is starting to age, the wood is completely original, and the wood to metal fit is perfect, this gun looks much better, and more "right" than most typical refinish jobs. So here's a chance to own a stunning looking early factory lettered deluxe 1894 in the best caliber and configuration at a fraction of what a completely original finish gun would cost. Perfect mechanical function, after market tapped for a receiver sight if you ever wanted to use one, and a very nice sharp bore. Marbles sights. Assembly numbers are correctly placed and match on the stock, lower tang, and buttplate. And it matches the original factory records at the Cody Museum,  Photos taken in extremely harsh outdoor light that magnifies every flaw and thins the look of the blue. If you need additional photos or have questions, please don't hesitate to ask here's my email rahmonstill1@outlook.com

title: For Sale:  K31 rifle
postcontent:
Arguably the most accurate of the WW2 battle rifles featuring the lightning fast, straight pull bolt action, chambered in 7.5 X 55 mm with a 23 ½ in. barrel. The 7.5 X 55 cartridge produces a very flat trajectory with approx.. 15-20% more muzzle energy than the standard 308 / 7.62 X 51 cartridge. There at least four sources for this cartridge.

 If you are a collector of military firearms or a hunter looking for rifle that will take almost any North American game, the K31 would be an excellent choice for your collection.

 The rifle shown below is the most accurate rifle I have ever owned. The K31 in original condition is inherently accurate but this rifle has also been pillar bedded and receiver bedded making it capable of even tighter shot groups. It will consistently shoot 1 MOA with Swiss GP11 surplus ammo (I have some of this for sale).

 This rifle was purchased from the importer as “Excellent” grade. It has 90%+ bluing, a bright shiny bore, a 6 round detachable magazine, and an incredibly smooth 3 ½ to 4 # trigger.

 As shown, the rifle is fitted with an easily removable, no mar bipod mount and scope mount made by Swiss St. Marie, and a Bushnell 3-9 scope. These items will be priced separately. Please ask for prices if you are interested.

 The beech stock has been respectively and lightly sanded to preserve all of the original contours and historical markings. It has 7 coats of hand rubbed Tung Oil giving it a beautiful and tough finish.

 I am asking $385 for the rifle stand alone. I will give a package price with the items listed above if you are interested.

 To see this rifle, or for more information, please contact Jim at REDACTED or email REDACTED .

 Thanks for your interest.
